description.p:
According to the invention, the method for measuring geometry deformations of a turbine component, especially of a rotor groove or blade root, the method comprises the steps of:
providing the turbine component, or rotor groove or blade root, respectively, with at least one measuring mark;
using the at least one measuring mark as a reference point in determining, in a first measurement, a length on said turbine component or rotor groove or blade root, respectively, prior to the turbine being placed into service;
operating the turbine for a period of time;
determining, in a second measurement, said length on said turbine component or rotor groove or blade root, respectively, using again said at least one measuring mark as a reference point, after said operating period; and
comparing the measured lengths of said first and the second measurement; and
determining an amount of creep deformation in said turbine component or rotor groove or blade root, respectively, based on a difference between said measured lengths.

